cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper is primarily focused on user space network drivers, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also discusses the implementation of these drivers in operating systems (cs.OS) and the impact on application performance (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper presents a case study of driver implementation using C code (cs.PL) and discusses the potential for using these drivers in virtual machines (cs.DC).
